<div xml:id="div-edition_1" class="edition"><div type="ed"><head/><lg> <note type="source" target="#right(418)">cf. YSv (PT p. 847): idaṃ yogarahasyañ ca na vācyaṃ mūrkhasannidhau || yogadeśas tu tatraiva ||</note><anchor xml:id="418"/><tl><app><lem wit="#ceteri">na</lem><rdg wit="#B #L">ni</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#E #P #U2">snehān na</lem><rdg wit="#ceteri">śnehān</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#E #P #U2"/><rdg wit="#B #L">nā</rdg><rdg wit="#D #N1 #N2">a</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#ceteri">bhayāl lo</lem><rdg wit="#E #U1">bhayān</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#B #D #L #U1">bhān na</lem><rdg wit="#N1 #N2">obhān</rdg><rdg wit="#P">lno</rdg><rdg wit="#U2">lon</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#ceteri"/><rdg wit="#P">om.</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#ceteri">mohān na</lem><rdg wit="#P">om.</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#ceteri"/><rdg wit="#P">om.</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#ceteri">dhānād ba</lem><rdg wit="#L">na dhanād</rdg><rdg wit="#P">om.</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#ceteri">lāt</lem><rdg wit="#B">balāta</rdg><rdg wit="#P">om.</rdg></app>/</tl> <tl><app><lem wit="#ceteri">na</lem><rdg wit="#P">om.</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#ceteri">maitrībhāvān na</lem><rdg wit="#N2">maitrībhāva</rdg><rdg wit="#D">maitrī</rdg><rdg wit="#P">bhāvān</rdg></app><note type="philcomm" target="#right(418)">A lenghty omission starts in <ref target="#D">D</ref> after the word <hi rend="italic">maitrī</hi>. The single omissions will not be recorded in the critical apparatus. The reader will be informed once the evidence of <ref target="#D">D</ref> resumes.</note><anchor xml:id="418"/><app><lem wit="#N1 #U1"/><rdg wit="#B #L #P #U2">no</rdg><rdg wit="#E">nau</rdg><rdg wit="#N2">nā</rdg><rdg wit="#D">om.</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#N1 #U1">dāsān na</lem><rdg wit="#P">dānān</rdg><rdg wit="#E">dāryān</rdg><rdg wit="#B #L">dānāt</rdg><rdg wit="#N2 #U2">dānān</rdg><rdg wit="#D">om.</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#ceteri"/><rdg wit="#D">om.</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#ceteri">sauṃdaryān na</lem><rdg wit="#P #N2">saudaryān</rdg><rdg wit="#L">sauṃdayan</rdg><rdg wit="#D">om.</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#ceteri"/><rdg wit="#L">ni</rdg><rdg wit="#D">om.</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#ceteri">sevanāt</lem><rdg wit="#U1">sevatā</rdg></app>// <otherlanguage><uproman>53</uproman>.1</otherlanguage> //</tl> </lg> <p> <app><lem wit="#P #N1 #N2 #U2">sāmānyād agre</lem><rdg wit="#B #E #L #U1">sāmānyāgre</rdg></app> yogo na <app><lem wit="#E #P #N1 #U1 #U2">kathanīyaḥ</lem><rdg wit="#B">kathaniyaṃ</rdg><rdg wit="#L">kathanīyaṃ</rdg><rdg wit="#N2">kanīyaḥ</rdg></app>/ <app><lem wit="#ceteri">yaḥ</lem><rdg wit="#U1">om.</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#ceteri">paranindā</lem><rdg wit="#B #L #U1">paraniṃdāṃ</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#ceteri">rato</lem><rdg wit="#B #L">om.</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#ceteri">bhavati</lem><rdg wit="#B #L">karoti</rdg></app>/ <app><lem wit="#ceteri">dūrācāro bhavati</lem><rdg wit="#B #L">om.</rdg></app>/ <app><lem wit="#P #U2">bhrātur mi</lem><rdg wit="#N1 #N2">bhrātu°</rdg><rdg wit="#U1">bhrātṛr</rdg><rdg wit="#B #E">dur°</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#ceteri">mitrasya</lem><rdg wit="#U1">mitraṃ</rdg><rdg wit="#B #E">maitryānyasya</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#N2 #U1">ca yogyaṃ</lem><rdg wit="#N1">ca yogyaṃ ca</rdg><rdg wit="#P #U2">yogyaṃ</rdg><rdg wit="#B #E">om.</rdg></app> vastu na dadāti/ <note type="philcomm" target="#right(420)">Sentence omitted in <ref target="#L"><selectlanguage>english</selectlanguage>L</ref>.</note><anchor xml:id="420"/><note type="source" target="#range(right(421),left(_421e))">cf. YSv (PT p. 847): stutir nindā na karttavyā sādhunā satyavādinā || yogānadhikāriṇam āha tatraiva ||</note><anchor xml:id="421"/><note type="philcomm" target="#range(right(422),left(_421e))">Both sentences omitted in <ref target="#B"><selectlanguage>english</selectlanguage>B</ref> and <ref target="#L"><selectlanguage>english</selectlanguage>L</ref>.</note><anchor xml:id="422"/><app><lem wit="#P #U2">yo</lem><rdg wit="#N1 #N2 #U1">so</rdg><rdg wit="#E">ya</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#ceteri">satyaṃ</lem><rdg wit="#E">asatyaṃ</rdg></app> vadati/ <app><lem wit="#E #P">yo</lem><rdg wit="#ceteri">om.</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#ceteri">yogināṃ</lem><rdg wit="#N1 #N2">yoginā</rdg><rdg wit="#E">yoga°</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#ceteri">manomadhye</lem><rdg wit="#E">om.</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#ceteri">nindāṃ</lem><rdg wit="#U1">ni°</rdg></app> karoti/<anchor xml:id="_421e"/> <note type="source" target="#range(right(423),left(_423e))">cf. YSv (PT p. 847): manomadhye dayā nāsti sadā yaḥ kalahapriyaḥ |</note><anchor xml:id="423"/>yasya manomadhye dayā na bhavati/ <note type="philcomm" target="#right(424)">Sentence omitted in <ref target="#D"><selectlanguage>english</selectlanguage>D</ref> and <ref target="#N2"><selectlanguage>english</selectlanguage>N<textsubscript>2</textsubscript></ref>.</note><anchor xml:id="424"/><app><lem wit="#E #N1 #U1">yaḥ</lem><rdg wit="#B #L #P #U2">yasya</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#E #P #N1 #U1">kalahapriyo</lem><rdg wit="#B #L">kalahaṃ priyo</rdg><rdg wit="#U2">kalahaḥ priyo</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#ceteri">bhavati</lem><rdg wit="#B #L">na bhavati</rdg></app>/<anchor xml:id="_423e"/> <app><lem wit="#E #P #U1 #U2">svakāryakaraṇe</lem><rdg wit="#L #N1">svakāryākaraṇe</rdg><rdg wit="#B">svakāryākaraṇeṃ</rdg><rdg wit="#N2">svakāryyākaraṇā</rdg></app> sāvadhāno bhavati/ <note type="source" target="#range(right(425),left(_425e))">cf. YSv (PT p. 847): svakāryalobhane śīlo gurukāryaparāṅmukhaḥ | etasmai ca na dātavyaṃ vaktavyaṃ tasya sannidhau |</note><anchor xml:id="425"/><app><lem wit="#ceteri">guroḥ</lem><rdg wit="#B #N2 #U2">guro</rdg></app> <app><lem resp="#ego" type="emendation">kāryakāraṇe</lem><rdg wit="#ceteri">kāryakaraṇe</rdg><rdg wit="#B">kārye karaṇe</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#P #U2">'nādṛto</lem><rdg wit="#N1 #N2 #U1">ādaro na</rdg><rdg wit="#B">anādarano</rdg><rdg wit="#L">anādare no</rdg><rdg wit="#E">na dattacitto</rdg></app> bhavati/ <app><lem wit="#ceteri">etādṛśasyāgre</lem><rdg wit="#U1">etādṛśasya agre</rdg></app> na <app><lem wit="#ceteri">yogaḥ</lem><rdg wit="#N1 #N2 #U1">om.</rdg></app> kriyate na <app><lem wit="#E #P #U1 #U2">paṭhyate</lem><rdg wit="#N1 #N2">padyaṃte</rdg><rdg wit="#B #L">paṭhayate</rdg></app>/<anchor xml:id="_425e"/> <app><lem wit="#N1 #L #U1">śṛṇvan gī</lem><rdg wit="#N2">śuśvana</rdg><rdg wit="#ceteri">śrṛṇvan</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#ceteri">tādikān</lem><rdg wit="#E">prītādikān</rdg></app>\dd <app><lem wit="#ceteri">śabdān pa</lem><rdg wit="#N2">śabdāt |</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#ceteri">śyan rū</lem><rdg wit="#U1">paśyat</rdg></app>paṃ manoharaṃ// <app><lem wit="#ceteri">jighran ga</lem><rdg wit="#E">jāgrat</rdg><rdg wit="#U1">jighraṃ</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#N1 #N2">gandhān su</lem><rdg wit="#P">gaṃdhāṃś ca</rdg><rdg wit="#U1">nāṃdhaś ca</rdg><rdg wit="#B #P">agachan</rdg><rdg wit="#U2">spṛśan gaṃdhan</rdg><rdg wit="#E">om.</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#U1 #U2">rabhīn spṛ</lem><rdg wit="#E">sphuran</rdg><rdg wit="#P #L">surabhin</rdg><rdg wit="#B">sphurabhi</rdg><rdg wit="#N1 #N2">śusurabhīn</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#Y">spṛśan spa</lem><rdg wit="#N1">spṛśyanasya</rdg><rdg wit="#N2">spṛśyanasyaṃ</rdg><rdg wit="#U1">om.</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#P #U1 #U2">n sparśaṃ</lem><rdg wit="#E">sparśa°</rdg><rdg wit="#ceteri">om.</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#ceteri">mṛḍupriyaṃ</lem><rdg wit="#N2">śarmṛdupriyaṃ</rdg><rdg wit="#U2">mṛḍu || priyaṃ</rdg></app>// svādān ma<app><lem wit="#ceteri">noramān khā</lem><rdg wit="#B #L">manorathān</rdg><rdg wit="#N1 #N2">manomān</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#ceteri">dan bhrā</lem><rdg wit="#B #L">khādavan</rdg><rdg wit="#U1">khādaṃta°</rdg><rdg wit="#N1">svādan</rdg><rdg wit="#E #N2">om.</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#ceteri">myan de</lem><rdg wit="#B #L">bhrāman</rdg><rdg wit="#N1">bhrāmyena</rdg><rdg wit="#N2">bhrāmya na</rdg></app><app><lem wit="#ceteri">śān ma</lem><rdg wit="#U1">tveṣāṃn</rdg></app>noramān// </p></div></div><div xml:id="div-translation_1" class="translation"><div type="trans"><head/><p> <paragraph><uproman>58</uproman>.1 </paragraph> Not because of love, not because of fear, not because of greed, not because of gift, not because of friendship, not because of hostility, not because of nobility, not because of service, shall yoga be taught in front of everyone. He, who loves it to blame others; who loves to criticise others; who is behaving badly; who does not gives [single] thing, which benefits friend and brother; who does not speak the truth and despises yoga in spirit; in whose mind compassion does not arise; who is one that delights in quarrel; attention arises for him regarding his selfish intentions; [and] disrespect arises towards the intentions of the teacher. In front of someone like this yoga is neither done nor taught.<note place="bottom">Show up to get things done!</note> While hearing the sound of music etc., while seeing heart pounding forms; while smelling fragnent scent, while touching lovely and soft touch, while eating food that pleases the mind, while travelling to beautiful places, \ldots \flushpage </p></div></div>
